                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="302011" author="zam" created="Wed, 19 May 2021 14:49:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It is an compatibility issue with an old app built against lustre-2.10, liblustreapi.so version is not yet added.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="301560" author="zam" created="Fri, 14 May 2021 05:50:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;James, yes you right. Apps should be linked with more specific libraries. There might be something wrong with the app build process.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="301490" author="simmonsja" created="Thu, 13 May 2021 15:18:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think this is broken. By the RPM spec liblustreapi.so goes into the devel package. Now if you can show me in the RPM specification that liblustreapi.so belongs in the main package then I will believe it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="301455" author="gerrit" created="Thu, 13 May 2021 12:04:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Alexander Zarochentsev (alexander.zarochentsev@hpe.com) uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/43695&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/43695&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
